Hong Kong stocks slip in London after a firm start . Hong Kong stocks gave up initial gains and were trading slightly lower in London in thin trading on Thursday . A strong showing on Wall Street on Wednesday boosted Hong Kong shares in early in the London trading session , dealers said . " The Dow came off at the open and we just sort of drifted lower , but there ' s absolutely no volume behind it , " a London dealer said . The Hang Seng London Reference index was down 29 . 26 to 12 , 486 . 97 at 1433 GMT , having climbed as high as 12 , 497 . 81 earlier . In Hong Kong , the Hang Seng index lost 65 . 08 points to close at 12 , 516 . 23 . 
